Pristina has said it is ready to declare it unilaterally if the Security Council does not decide in its favour.
Belgrade insists on greater autonomy.
"Unfortunately, no agreement has been reached", said the president of the Kosovo Autonomous Authority, Fatmir Sejdiu, at the Baden hotel where the last-chance negotiations had been taking place since Monday.
Hashim Thaci, former commander of the Kosovo rebellion and future premier of the province, expressed his regret.
But he added that the autonomy plan presented by Belgrade was "a part of the past that led to murders and deportations".
 The domino effect
