The Spanish gendarmerie arrested the mayor of the Murcian town of Totana, the "popular" José Martínez Andreo, the head of the local police, the secretary of the town hall and a hotel entrepreneur suspected of possible urban crimes, sources from the investigation informed today.
The city councillor was arrested at his home and taken to the town hall, where many officials were now meeting, who also presented themselves to the Municipal Planning Councillor and the municipal company for the management of industrial land and housing.
These three decisions are in addition to the six decisions made last Monday in the provinces of Galicia, Murcia and Madrid, in an operation to requalify more than 2 million hectares of agricultural land for urbanisation so that the Galician company Nuaria can build 4,000 housing units, after paying illegal commissions during the last parliamentary term.
